By: Delegate Moon
Introduced and read first time: January 30, 2025
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Department of Transportation – Electric Vehicle Charging
3 Infrastructure Expansion – Plans and Programs
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Transportation, in consultation
5 with the Maryland Energy Administration, to make certain estimations and
6 determinations regarding electric vehicles and electric vehicle charging
7 infrastructure; requiring the Department, in consultation with the Maryland Energy
8 Administration, to develop plans and implement programs to increase the electric
9 vehicle charging infrastructure in the State; and generally relating to electric
10 vehicles and electric vehicle charging infrastructure.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Transportation
13 Section 2–114
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Transportation
19 2–114.
20 (A) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND ENERGY
21 ADMINISTRATION, SHALL:
22 (1) ESTIMATE THE NUMBER OF ELECTRIC VEHICLES IN OPERATION
23 IN THE STATE NECESSARY TO ACHIEVE THE GOALS OF § 2–1205(C)(2) OF THE
24 ENVIRONMENT ARTICLE; AND
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
