1 (2) ESTIMATE THE NUMBER AND DETERMINE THE DENSITY AND
2 LOCATION OF PUBLIC AND PRIVATE ELECTRIC VEHICLE CHARGING STATIONS
3 NECESSARY TO CONVENIENTLY SUSTAIN THE NUMBER OF VEHICLES ESTIMATED
4 UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
5 (B) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND ENERGY
6 ADMINISTRATION:
7 (1) SHALL DEVELOP PLANS AND IMPLEMENT PROGRAMS TO
8 INCREASE THE ELECTRIC VEHICLE CHARGING INFRASTRUCTURE NECESSARY TO
9 ACHIEVE THE GOALS OF § 2–1205(C)(2) OF THE ENVIRONMENT ARTICLE AND
10 SUPPORT THE NUMBER OF VEHICLES ESTIMATED UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1) OF
11 THIS SECTION; AND
12 (2) MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THE PLANS AND
13 PROGRAMS DEVELOPED UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2025.

